ll molecules using the assigned ice modes. Computer modeling in conjunction with ab initio calculations was used to analyze and interpret adsorbate spectra and to elucidate the influence of factors such as the extent of surface disorder on gas-surface interactions. The results suggest significant modification of the ice surface structure with respect to the cubic crystalline interior, toward loss of lateral order.},
